  "body": "Opening the issue after talking to @0mkara who is behind react-native-geth and asked me about:\r\n\r\n`err \"context deadline exceeded`\r\n\r\nand the geth team. The main problem here is that this is logged as an error - should be logged as info or warning as there is nothing a developer consuming geth can do here but it can happen e.g. when a peer disapeers (pun intended) which can and will happen in a p2p network. But this needs serious work on the go-mobile logging framework and is not high priority as there are bigger fishes to fry still. Mainly opening this issue to not loose track of this and maybe give hints to developers searching for this error.\r\n\r\n",
