    "body": "I think in order to progress on this, we need to better understand how logging works in general on Android. If anyone could chip in with a tiny explanation, it would be great.\r\n\r\nCurrently within go-ethereum we use `gomobile` to create the Go->Java bindings. The binding generator takes whatever is output to `stderr` and converts it to error logs (and maybe `stdout` is converted to info logs?). As such, the way the mobile framework currently logs is that our Go logger just prints whatever to `stdout`, which gets picked up by `gomobile` and fed into `logcat`.\r\n\r\nA better alternative would be to expand the `log` package with an `AndroidHandler`, so that when a log is being raised, we don't blindly dump it into `stderr` with the `StreamHandler`, rather we can call platform APIs directly on `logcat`.\r\n\r\nThis shoudn't be too much work really, just needs a bit of Android experience, a bit of logger framework investigation, and the ability to use and test results via `gomobile`.",
