    "body": "Logging in android is done with a call to static methods the Log class: \r\n\r\nhttps://developer.android.com/reference/android/util/Log\r\n\r\nthe method used determines the log-level. \r\nFor libraries it is also nice if they do not directly log this way but use a logging framework (slf4j is widely used but I am more a fan of [timber](https://github.com/JakeWharton/timber)) - to give consuming apps more control (e.g. interceptions like log to remote or suppressing logs)",
